(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

00:56.507 --> 00:57.849
(SLAPS)

01:00.219 --> 01:01.436
(THUDS)

01:13.733 --> 01:18.784
(EERIE MUSIC)

01:20.031 --> 01:21.453
(GRUNTS)

01:43.262 --> 01:44.747
(SCREAMS)

01:44.847 --> 01:45.998
(THUDS)

01:46.098 --> 01:47.724
(THUNDERING)

01:52.855 --> 01:56.234
(SCREAMING)

02:05.618 --> 02:08.496
(GROANING)

02:10.122 --> 02:11.418
(THUNDERING)

02:13.709 --> 02:15.381
(THUNDERING)

02:20.508 --> 02:23.102
(THUNDERING)

02:29.934 --> 02:35.361
(SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC)

03:52.725 --> 03:58.106
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

04:03.694 --> 04:06.822
What a beautiful city Guanajuato is.

04:07.489 --> 04:09.892
My husbands told me a lot about it.

04:09.992 --> 04:12.520
He probably missed you very much.

04:12.620 --> 04:16.589
He's sorry he couldn't pick you up
at the airport, but, uh...

04:16.707 --> 04:18.423
he couldn't leave the mine.

04:18.584 --> 04:20.986
Mines are very jealous.

04:21.086 --> 04:23.554
Like most females.

04:25.049 --> 04:27.535
(LAUGHS) Is a mine a female, Pepe?

04:27.635 --> 04:32.164
Yes. No matter how hard you try,
a mine won't surrender.

04:32.264 --> 04:33.582
If you're not lucky.

04:33.682 --> 04:34.708
Come on, Pepe.

04:34.808 --> 04:37.231
Let's go to the mine right away.

04:38.395 --> 04:43.822
(FOREBODING MUSIC)

05:02.544 --> 05:03.696
Well...

05:03.796 --> 05:06.365
Here you are, at your mine.

05:06.465 --> 05:08.137
Good.

05:09.218 --> 05:12.187
I'm going to look for my husband.

05:13.555 --> 05:18.982
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

05:24.692 --> 05:30.119
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

05:43.085 --> 05:44.962
(CLUNKING)

05:51.885 --> 05:53.412
(SCREAMING)

05:53.512 --> 05:54.538
Jen!

05:54.638 --> 05:56.665
(OVERLAPPING CHATTERING)

05:56.765 --> 05:58.209
Are you alright?

05:58.309 --> 05:59.981
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

06:00.644 --> 06:02.691
(EXCITED INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

06:03.022 --> 06:04.548
Look at their faces.

06:04.648 --> 06:06.926
They're scared to death of a corpse.

06:07.026 --> 06:08.636
Mr. Baines.

06:08.736 --> 06:09.678
MARK: Pepe, what is it?

06:09.778 --> 06:10.930
PEPE: Look.

06:11.030 --> 06:12.622
Silver.

06:14.950 --> 06:16.602
I knew it!

06:16.702 --> 06:19.271
If he found it, we can find it!
I know it, I know it!

06:19.371 --> 06:20.918
Then he died.

06:21.498 --> 06:24.276
Nobody can take silver out of La Quemada.

06:24.376 --> 06:25.945
Dammit, you don't believe
that crap, do ya?

06:26.045 --> 06:28.781
No left hand. Somebody stole his hand.

06:28.881 --> 06:29.907
What does that mean?

06:30.007 --> 06:31.700
It's nothing. Superstition. It's nothing.

06:31.800 --> 06:33.827
Come on, let's get out of here.

06:34.803 --> 06:36.997
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING IN SPANISH)

06:37.097 --> 06:39.458
The mummies I wanna watch 'em.

06:39.558 --> 06:41.669
Mexico is a crude hill.

06:41.769 --> 06:45.902
Which kind of blows the theory of die
young and have a beautiful corpse.

06:53.614 --> 06:55.582
Poor things.

07:00.287 --> 07:02.356
Do you see that they
don't have any left hands?

07:02.456 --> 07:03.957
That's just like our mummy.

07:04.500 --> 07:05.901
La mano del diablo.

07:06.001 --> 07:07.778
The devil's hand.

07:07.878 --> 07:11.156
They say it first came out of hell
from La Quemada.

07:11.256 --> 07:14.493
It's a legend, but for our elders,
this was their truth.

07:14.593 --> 07:16.954
How about the truth of today?

07:17.054 --> 07:20.708
Today our fantasies
are much more sophisticated.

07:20.808 --> 07:22.543
Yes, like, uh...

07:22.643 --> 07:24.895
dreaming of oil.

07:25.938 --> 07:28.486
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING IN SPANISH)

07:34.905 --> 07:36.640
All right. Okay.

07:36.740 --> 07:37.850
What are these?

07:37.950 --> 07:40.978
It's, uh, candy made in the shape
of mummies. That's what they are.

07:41.078 --> 07:44.148
- They're, um, mummy yummies.
- Oh, how macabre.

07:44.248 --> 07:46.295
Yeah. But do you want one?

07:46.708 --> 07:49.006
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

08:00.681 --> 08:02.583
- We have problems.
- JENNIFER: What's the matter?

08:02.683 --> 08:05.169
They're not gonna work, and they're
not gonna let anyone else work.

08:05.269 --> 08:07.737
So you better get outta here, quick.

08:12.484 --> 08:14.011
I've got an idea.

08:14.111 --> 08:15.929
We're gonna go down into the mine.

08:16.029 --> 08:18.849
You and I. We're gonna
go down into the lowest level.

08:18.949 --> 08:22.061
If they see a woman going down there
and coming back safely,

08:22.161 --> 08:24.163
how can they refuse?

08:27.124 --> 08:28.108
Come on.

08:28.208 --> 08:30.676
Besides, you and I can be alone.

08:32.421 --> 08:34.013
Come on.

08:35.549 --> 08:40.976
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

08:54.193 --> 08:58.700
I think I'm going to have to...
to hold on here.

09:00.032 --> 09:02.330
MARK: This is really steep.

09:04.620 --> 09:06.563
How deep is this?

09:06.663 --> 09:08.649
- MARK: Deep.
- Yeah?

09:08.749 --> 09:12.677
MARK: Oh, God... They've been digging
this mine for over 300 years.

09:13.504 --> 09:15.551
Listen to this.

09:16.924 --> 09:18.283
(GRUNTS)

09:18.383 --> 09:20.931
(ROCK CLATTERING)

09:27.643 --> 09:30.145
Probably go on for half an hour.

09:31.813 --> 09:37.240
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

09:39.696 --> 09:41.948
(ROCKS CLATTERING)

09:53.919 --> 09:58.925
- (OMINOUS MUSIC)
- (WATER DRIPPING)

09:59.591 --> 10:01.058
(THUDS)

10:04.388 --> 10:07.082
You think, you think maybe they're, uh...

10:07.182 --> 10:09.150
right about that legend?

10:09.643 --> 10:11.986
God, I hope they're not.

10:13.313 --> 10:18.740
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

10:29.329 --> 10:32.691
It's funny. You know,
Pepe never brought me down here.

10:32.791 --> 10:35.297
This must be it.
This is what they're afraid of.

10:36.587 --> 10:38.930
JENNIFER: This is a torture chamber.

10:39.339 --> 10:41.074
MARK: Wow. Look at this.

10:41.174 --> 10:44.511
Must be... hundreds of years old.

10:49.683 --> 10:51.105
(SCREAMS)

10:53.770 --> 10:55.192
Oh.

10:55.814 --> 10:57.299
What are you collecting those?

10:57.399 --> 10:59.676
Oh, let's go back. Listen,
I'm getting scared.

10:59.776 --> 11:00.719
It's all right.
Now wait just a few minutes.

11:00.819 --> 11:03.617
I wanna see what's down here. (GRUNTS)

11:07.409 --> 11:09.436
(GROANS) It's all right.

11:09.536 --> 11:12.648
Take it easy. Now just... get something.

11:12.748 --> 11:16.129
Get, get a board or something. I'm...
I can't get outta here.

11:16.543 --> 11:18.260
Get a board!

11:18.712 --> 11:20.304
Hurry up!

11:21.214 --> 11:22.491
Oh!

11:22.591 --> 11:23.408
Hurry up!

11:23.508 --> 11:26.181
Oh, Mark! (SCREAMS)

11:27.638 --> 11:29.060
(THUDDING)

11:34.227 --> 11:38.948
(EERIE MUSIC)

11:39.441 --> 11:40.737
Jenny!

11:40.859 --> 11:42.906
Where are you?

11:43.320 --> 11:46.640
I'm in some kind of a... chamber.

11:46.740 --> 11:48.100
How can I get down?

11:48.200 --> 11:50.477
MARK:
There's a ladder over here. I'll use that.

11:50.577 --> 11:51.953
Okay.

12:06.301 --> 12:07.452
MARK: See it?

12:07.552 --> 12:08.495
JENNIFER: Yes.

12:08.595 --> 12:10.688
MARK: (GRUNTING) Come on down.

12:11.014 --> 12:12.640
JENNIFER: Okay.

12:19.272 --> 12:21.490
I'm gonna slide the last bit.

12:23.527 --> 12:25.119
Oh.

12:30.575 --> 12:33.077
Darling, you're all right.

12:33.704 --> 12:35.421
Look at that.

12:35.622 --> 12:37.669
Look at that!

12:40.669 --> 12:42.921
Oh. Incredible.

12:43.130 --> 12:45.678
This place is incredible.

12:50.178 --> 12:51.975
What's that?

12:52.264 --> 12:53.373
(SNIFFS) It's oil.

12:53.473 --> 12:55.316
Get some light here.

13:14.035 --> 13:16.879
What do you think this is?

13:18.165 --> 13:21.943
I think it's a cultist temple

13:22.043 --> 13:23.669
for devil worshipers.

13:23.795 --> 13:25.421
Well...

13:28.800 --> 13:30.267
Little babies.

13:30.802 --> 13:33.225
I mean these gotta be rank.

13:33.555 --> 13:36.558
This statue is missing a hand too.

13:37.142 --> 13:38.939
Let's get out of here.

13:41.605 --> 13:45.075
Oh, God, this place is really creepy.

13:47.027 --> 13:49.029
Look at this, darling.

13:49.529 --> 13:50.555
Oh, I shouldn't touch it.

13:50.655 --> 13:52.247
Why not?

13:53.200 --> 13:54.559
Prove we've been down here.

13:54.659 --> 13:57.082
To show these guys
there's nothing to be afraid of.

13:58.163 --> 14:02.216
Well, if this mine is cursed,
here's their demon.

14:03.835 --> 14:05.587
Right.

14:07.214 --> 14:08.556
Devil!

14:09.508 --> 14:12.306
We have broken your curse!

14:13.220 --> 14:15.768
JENNIFER: Well, now the miners
will have to come back to work.

14:16.598 --> 14:18.395
Vamonos.

14:21.478 --> 14:22.854
(THUNDERING)

14:28.485 --> 14:30.303
Here! Here's your devil's hand!

14:30.403 --> 14:32.746
Pepe, tell them they can go back to work!

14:33.657 --> 14:35.534
Nothing to be afraid of.

14:36.535 --> 14:38.878
Nothing to be afraid of!

14:39.621 --> 14:41.898
Whats the matter with you? Huh?

14:41.998 --> 14:43.150
What's the matter?

14:43.250 --> 14:44.876
All right, then!

14:45.335 --> 14:47.087
Go away!

14:47.546 --> 14:50.174
I'll get someone else to work this mine!

14:56.221 --> 14:57.664
JENNIFER: Don't give up.

14:57.764 --> 14:59.481
Do you know what I've done?

15:01.101 --> 15:03.774
Do you realize all the money I borrowed?

15:04.604 --> 15:07.132
I feel like some fool.

15:07.232 --> 15:10.719
Takes all his grandmother's money,
and goes to Las Vegas and loses it all.

15:10.819 --> 15:12.992
Then blows his brains out.

15:19.911 --> 15:22.539
It's going to be all right.

15:23.707 --> 15:25.800
Look, I have a surprise.

15:26.501 --> 15:28.403
Some champagne.

15:28.503 --> 15:30.004
For us.

15:37.721 --> 15:39.331
Your eyes.

15:39.431 --> 15:41.433
You're beautiful.

15:41.683 --> 15:46.939
(SLOW ROMANTIC MUSIC)

15:56.156 --> 16:01.537
(SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC)

16:08.877 --> 16:10.549
(THUDS)

16:22.182 --> 16:23.729
(THUNDERING)

16:35.028 --> 16:36.450
(CLATTERS)

16:40.992 --> 16:46.419
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

17:03.556 --> 17:08.983
(EERIE MUSIC)

17:24.577 --> 17:30.004
(EERIE MUSIC)

17:41.136 --> 17:43.730
(HEARTBEATS)

18:00.947 --> 18:03.950
(HEARTBEATS)

18:16.296 --> 18:18.764
(HEARTBEATS)

18:43.239 --> 18:45.207
(HEARTBEATS)

19:02.592 --> 19:04.969
(GASPS) Mark! (SCREAMS)

19:08.932 --> 19:10.729
(GROANS)

19:11.601 --> 19:13.318
Oh, God!

19:16.356 --> 19:18.529
(THUNDERING)

19:25.406 --> 19:27.658
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

19:37.710 --> 19:39.928
Must've been a nightmare or something.

19:40.588 --> 19:41.531
(EXHALES)

19:41.631 --> 19:43.178
That wasn't a nightmare.

19:43.341 --> 19:45.388
Just a dream, that's all.

19:46.928 --> 19:49.601
JENNIFER: That hand grabbed you.

20:05.864 --> 20:10.835
(EERIE MUSIC)

20:12.996 --> 20:15.464
Let me see your hand.

20:20.211 --> 20:21.154
Get that thing away from me.

20:21.254 --> 20:22.238
Show me your hand.

20:22.338 --> 20:23.680
Take that thing away from me.

20:25.258 --> 20:26.326
What's wrong?

20:26.426 --> 20:28.269
Stay away from me.

20:29.429 --> 20:31.146
Mark.

20:37.478 --> 20:41.232
(EERIE MUSIC)

20:43.234 --> 20:45.953
Oh, my God.

20:51.993 --> 20:53.561
Pepe, is my husband here?

20:53.661 --> 20:55.355
PEPE: Yes, he's here.

20:55.455 --> 20:57.899
He took the men into the mine.

20:57.999 --> 21:00.026
You mean, they went back into the mine?

21:00.126 --> 21:02.362
PEPE: Si, señora. He's crazy.

21:02.462 --> 21:04.339
He pushed them to go down there.

21:12.597 --> 21:13.498
Mark!

21:13.598 --> 21:15.520
Please, don't do this!

21:17.727 --> 21:20.275
No, Mark! Don't!

21:21.064 --> 21:22.941
(EXPLODING)

21:25.735 --> 21:27.703
(EXPLODING)

21:30.657 --> 21:33.785
(EXPLODING, RUMBLING)

21:35.954 --> 21:38.081
(EXPLODING)

21:40.541 --> 21:45.968
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

21:59.352 --> 22:04.779
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

22:09.279 --> 22:13.409
(INDISTINCT EXCITED CHATTERING)

22:24.961 --> 22:27.509
(OVERLAPPING SHOUTS AND CHEERING)

22:38.474 --> 22:40.585
You outta have great luck now, big man.

22:40.685 --> 22:44.005
Look what just stand
along side of you here.

22:44.105 --> 22:45.089
Lady luck?

22:45.189 --> 22:46.531
Lady luck.

22:51.571 --> 22:54.039
(EXCITED SHOUTING)

22:54.866 --> 22:56.492
Lucky seven.

22:59.871 --> 23:02.749
(CLAPPING AND SHOUTING)

23:09.363 --> 23:11.706
Give me five grand on a pass.

23:12.383 --> 23:14.681
Woah, we got a big better here.

23:16.804 --> 23:17.830
What do ya say? What do ya say?

23:17.930 --> 23:19.749
How about the hard low?

23:19.849 --> 23:22.602
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

23:24.312 --> 23:26.256
Hey! That's what I'm lookin' for.

23:26.356 --> 23:28.028
Let that ride.

23:28.191 --> 23:29.738
Let it ride.

23:30.818 --> 23:36.245
(SLOW MUSIC)

23:42.997 --> 23:47.502
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

23:50.380 --> 23:51.864
- Hello.
- CLERK: Yes, madam?

23:51.964 --> 23:56.518
My name is Mrs. Mark Baines,
and I wondered if you've seen this man.

23:56.719 --> 23:58.705
Mm. Another Mrs. Mark Baines.

23:58.805 --> 24:01.666
If you knew how many Mrs. Baines
have been in this hotel today,

24:01.766 --> 24:04.360
you'd lie down on the floor
and laugh yourself silly.

24:05.061 --> 24:07.588
Well, I'm sorry,
but I am Mrs. Jennifer Baines,

24:07.688 --> 24:09.841
and my husband is in trouble.

24:09.941 --> 24:10.842
Well...

24:10.942 --> 24:12.343
I'm sorry, madam.

24:12.443 --> 24:15.888
It's a policy of this hotel not to give
out information about hotel residents.

24:15.988 --> 24:17.682
If you'd like to contact him
through the house phones,

24:17.782 --> 24:19.909
they're right around the corner.

24:34.507 --> 24:37.726
-Yes, Mr. Mark Baines, please.

24:39.679 --> 24:42.056
He's not taking any calls?

24:42.890 --> 24:45.688
Well, would you mind paging him, please?

24:47.520 --> 24:50.273
VOICEOVER: Mr. Mark Baines.
Call the operator, please.

24:52.733 --> 24:55.452
STICKMAN: Number seven, a winner.
He's coming out again.

24:55.862 --> 24:58.114
(EXCITED CHATTERING)

24:58.865 --> 25:00.992
One more seven, shooter.

25:03.369 --> 25:04.961
All right.

25:07.915 --> 25:09.734
- All right. What do we want?
- Seven.

25:09.834 --> 25:11.736
Seven, huh? You want a seven?

25:11.836 --> 25:13.196
- Yeah, I'd like a seven.
- MARK: Blow on 'em, blow on 'em.

25:13.296 --> 25:14.447
(BLOWS) Hey!

25:14.547 --> 25:16.549
Give me a three!

25:17.717 --> 25:20.936
Hey, I like that three.

25:25.683 --> 25:28.311
STICKMAN: Everything goes. Everything.

25:28.811 --> 25:30.338
MARK:
You should never use another man's luck.

25:30.438 --> 25:32.485
Never use another man's luck. (LAUGHS)

25:36.486 --> 25:38.554
(SLOT MACHINES CLANKING)

25:38.654 --> 25:40.807
VOICEOVER:
Mr. Joe DeAngelo telephone call.

25:40.907 --> 25:42.249
Joe DeAngelo...

25:45.328 --> 25:47.188
Listen, you don't have
to do more gambling, do you?

25:47.288 --> 25:48.689
- MARK: No, no.
- My car is right here.

25:48.789 --> 25:50.791
MARK: All right, let's go.
C'mon, c'mon let's go.

25:52.502 --> 25:57.178
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

26:00.384 --> 26:01.976
(THUDS)

26:02.136 --> 26:04.263
- FRANKIE: Unlock the door!
- (CAR ENGINE STARTS)

26:13.564 --> 26:15.816
All right, let's go.

26:19.320 --> 26:24.701
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

26:49.475 --> 26:50.835
Take the car down the road and hide it.

26:50.935 --> 26:52.652
Okay, honey.

26:54.230 --> 26:56.277
(CAR RETREATING)

26:58.442 --> 27:01.115
(LOUD MUSIC, INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

27:10.580 --> 27:11.606
This dude's clean.

27:11.706 --> 27:13.566
He hasn't got an apparatus on him.

27:13.666 --> 27:14.358
Nothing.

27:14.458 --> 27:15.610
Not a thing.

27:15.710 --> 27:16.319
You think he's all right?

27:16.419 --> 27:17.570
He's all right.

27:17.670 --> 27:20.198
You okay? Huh?

27:20.298 --> 27:22.241
- ANGELA: Wake up.
- FRANKIE: Well, there he is.

27:22.341 --> 27:25.094
ANGELA: Wake up, bozo. Let's go.

27:27.430 --> 27:30.917
MARK: Lucky. You went the wrong way.

27:31.017 --> 27:33.940
The money's at the safe at the casino.

27:34.604 --> 27:37.903
We don't want your money, pinhead.

27:38.399 --> 27:39.842
FRANKIE: I wanna know how you did it.

27:39.942 --> 27:43.195
MARK:
Do what? Meet such attractive people?

27:43.529 --> 27:44.472
No, no.

27:44.572 --> 27:48.100
I wanna know how you threw 23 straight
passes without switching the dice.

27:48.200 --> 27:49.977
(THUDS) That's what I wanna know.

27:50.077 --> 27:51.954
How'd you do that?

27:54.582 --> 27:56.379
Beginner's luck.

27:56.876 --> 27:59.003
Well, let me tell you about luck.

27:59.837 --> 28:03.157
There's an easy way, and a hard way.

28:03.257 --> 28:05.009
Now, the easy way,

28:05.259 --> 28:07.703
you tell us, we'll let you go.

28:07.803 --> 28:10.101
We'll all cash in. Rich.

28:11.140 --> 28:13.392
And the hard way?

28:14.018 --> 28:14.919
(THUDS)

28:15.019 --> 28:17.630
I'll cut those hands off,
and feed 'em to the coyotes.

28:17.730 --> 28:20.007
- That's...
- Fool! Like a fool!

28:20.107 --> 28:21.467
(SCREAMS)

28:21.567 --> 28:23.444
Get him, Frankie!

28:23.944 --> 28:24.679
(THUDS)

28:24.779 --> 28:26.055
Get him, Frankie!

28:26.155 --> 28:27.702
Frankie!

28:27.865 --> 28:29.617
(SCREAMING)

28:30.618 --> 28:32.228
Let me outta here! Get me outta...

28:32.328 --> 28:33.521
MARK: Shut up!

28:33.621 --> 28:34.605
Stay away from me!

28:34.705 --> 28:37.024
- Shut up!
- Stay away! (SCREAMS)

28:37.124 --> 28:39.797
(CRUSHING, MUFFLED CRIES)

28:40.670 --> 28:42.968
(GAGGING)

28:49.178 --> 28:54.605
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

29:00.731 --> 29:03.074
(ZAPPING)

29:05.820 --> 29:11.201
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

29:19.166 --> 29:21.009
(GRUNTING)

29:33.597 --> 29:36.145
(THUNDERING)

29:41.856 --> 29:44.199
(YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

29:48.529 --> 29:50.201
(THUNDERING)

29:59.165 --> 30:02.009
(CRYING OUT)

30:03.919 --> 30:07.013
(SCREAMING) Ah!

30:20.352 --> 30:22.980
We've got good news and bad news.

30:23.314 --> 30:24.799
Go ahead.

30:24.899 --> 30:26.821
Well, they found the girl.

30:28.110 --> 30:29.862
Dead.

30:30.237 --> 30:31.863
Oh.

30:32.448 --> 30:34.040
Where?

30:34.200 --> 30:36.577
About 20 miles across the state line.

30:37.661 --> 30:39.772
There are two other bodies nearby.

30:39.872 --> 30:40.773
Were they men?

30:40.873 --> 30:42.215
SGT. NEEDHAM: Yeah, both.

30:42.416 --> 30:43.776
One was a gambler.

30:43.876 --> 30:45.298
His name was name was Frankie Phillips.

30:46.086 --> 30:47.405
He's got the usual rap sheet.

30:47.505 --> 30:48.739
Extortion, fraud.

30:48.839 --> 30:50.932
Who was the other one?

30:52.176 --> 30:53.869
(SIGHS) Well, he was badly burned.

30:53.969 --> 30:56.722
They assume it's the owner
of a neighboring shack.

30:59.141 --> 31:01.063
That was Mark.

31:01.936 --> 31:03.421
Well...

31:03.521 --> 31:07.150
Some relative supposedly
identified the body.

31:07.650 --> 31:09.760
Anyway, they shipped it
to Los Angeles for burial.

31:09.860 --> 31:12.237
To Our Lady of Hope Cemetery in Inglewood.

31:12.571 --> 31:14.664
Might want to check that out.

31:15.866 --> 31:17.351
I will.

31:17.451 --> 31:21.000
Confusion, Father, stirring inside of me.

31:21.163 --> 31:22.755
Father...

31:23.207 --> 31:25.550
I ask your forbearance.

31:26.293 --> 31:29.405
I ask deliverance from doubt.

31:29.505 --> 31:30.676
Amen.

31:38.264 --> 31:39.623
Madam.

31:39.723 --> 31:41.975
I'm sorry, but the church is closed.

31:42.935 --> 31:44.211
Oh.

31:44.311 --> 31:47.109
I didn't know God punched a clock.

31:47.273 --> 31:48.632
No.

31:48.732 --> 31:51.552
No, he's available to anyone, at anytime.

31:51.652 --> 31:55.371
His emissaries though are...
are merely human.

31:55.990 --> 31:56.974
Good.

31:57.074 --> 32:01.124
Because then you'll understand
the problems of another human being.

32:01.996 --> 32:04.398
The man you buried was my husband.

32:04.498 --> 32:05.816
Did you ever see the body?

32:05.916 --> 32:07.133
FATHER CUNNINGHAM: No.

32:07.376 --> 32:09.945
Was an autopsy ever performed?

32:10.045 --> 32:11.864
Well, it wasn't necessary.

32:11.964 --> 32:14.967
The poor man was burnt beyond recognition.

32:15.134 --> 32:18.558
I'm going to insist
that the grave be opened.

32:18.721 --> 32:21.290
Well, you'll have to talk
to all the officials.

32:21.390 --> 32:25.735
You know, basically, the unearthing
of a body is, is legally complex.

32:26.729 --> 32:29.197
You're gonna need
a good reason, Mrs. Baines.

32:29.648 --> 32:31.866
That's perfectly all right.

32:34.653 --> 32:37.497
May I see the grave now, please, Father?

32:37.781 --> 32:42.832
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

32:43.829 --> 32:45.797
(EXPLODING)

32:48.292 --> 32:50.402
I'm sorry to have been
so brusque just now,

32:50.502 --> 32:53.175
but it's very urgent that I see his grave.

32:53.672 --> 32:55.924
-I understand, Mrs. Baines.

32:56.634 --> 33:00.955
You might gain some solace
from just being near the grave.

33:01.055 --> 33:02.581
Let's see now. Where are we.

33:02.681 --> 33:05.149
Some place close by here.

33:05.351 --> 33:06.727
Right.

33:07.645 --> 33:08.671
Here we are.

33:08.771 --> 33:10.214
Uh-oh.

33:10.314 --> 33:13.634
What sort of a disturbed person
would violate a grave?

33:13.734 --> 33:14.635
He did it.

33:14.735 --> 33:17.283
My husband, the man that you buried.

33:18.322 --> 33:20.057
This grave was not dug up.

33:20.157 --> 33:22.518
It was dug out, from the inside.

33:22.618 --> 33:25.086
Look, Father, there are no shovel marks.

33:26.664 --> 33:30.008
The earth was heaved up and out.

33:30.417 --> 33:31.735
And the coffin. Look.

33:31.835 --> 33:34.280
The wood is splintered,
just as if it had exploded.

33:34.380 --> 33:35.722
Hm.

33:36.423 --> 33:38.117
Well, uh...

33:38.217 --> 33:40.264
Come on, let's go.

33:43.055 --> 33:44.898
You coming?

33:50.896 --> 33:52.488
Wait!

34:00.239 --> 34:02.099
You blessed the grave.

34:02.199 --> 34:03.642
Evil defiled it.

34:03.742 --> 34:06.103
Now, is that a personal defeat
that you cannot accept?

34:06.203 --> 34:08.397
I cannot accept your whole theory.

34:08.496 --> 34:09.648
And yours?

34:09.748 --> 34:11.567
Well, your husband won a lot of money.

34:11.667 --> 34:13.819
Perhaps he made some enemies.

34:13.918 --> 34:16.045
Why would they want his body?

34:16.714 --> 34:20.618
There is no proof that the body
I laid to rest was your husbands.

34:20.717 --> 34:23.036
It was Mark's body.

34:23.137 --> 34:25.706
Graves have been vandalized before.

34:25.806 --> 34:27.373
Vandalized?

34:27.474 --> 34:30.085
Unfortunately,
they will be vandalized again.

34:30.185 --> 34:33.755
Just as long as priests remain blind.

34:33.856 --> 34:37.487
It's apparent to me
that the police should be notified.

34:38.444 --> 34:40.571
(RECEDING FOOTSTEPS)

34:48.661 --> 34:50.731
That's aisle three, section one.

34:50.831 --> 34:52.983
You'll find what's left of the grave.

34:53.083 --> 34:54.902
Yeah, I'll take a quick look.

34:55.002 --> 34:56.737
Say, tell me, Leo.

34:56.837 --> 34:58.781
What exactly do you hope to find?

34:58.881 --> 35:00.115
LEO: I really don't know.

35:00.215 --> 35:02.308
These kind of creeps really get me down.

35:02.760 --> 35:04.307
Goodnight.

35:06.263 --> 35:11.690
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

35:53.644 --> 35:55.004
Father.

35:55.104 --> 35:58.924
Do you believe that God
is the ultimate source of good?

35:59.024 --> 36:00.467
That's not a serious question.

36:00.567 --> 36:01.989
JENNIFER: Do you?

36:02.152 --> 36:03.470
What's your point?

36:03.570 --> 36:08.475
My point is that if you do, you must
believe in an evil force opposing God.

36:08.575 --> 36:11.123
Capable of causing destruction.

36:11.495 --> 36:15.274
Not in the form
of a 300-year-old hand that crawls.

36:15.374 --> 36:16.500
No!

36:21.713 --> 36:23.214
(THUDS)

36:24.091 --> 36:29.518
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

36:32.391 --> 36:34.313
(CAR HORN HONKING)

36:37.521 --> 36:42.948
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

37:01.128 --> 37:06.225
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

37:07.509 --> 37:09.135
- (THUNDERING)
- (GUN SHOTS)

37:17.186 --> 37:18.983
You stay here!

37:21.523 --> 37:26.950
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

37:34.411 --> 37:36.003
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

37:39.666 --> 37:41.418
Leo!

37:47.257 --> 37:48.633
What's that?

38:10.864 --> 38:13.241
JENNIFER: The devil's hand.

38:17.120 --> 38:18.997
(THUMPING)

38:32.761 --> 38:34.353
Hi, Leo.

38:40.602 --> 38:42.274
(THUMPS)

38:46.358 --> 38:48.326
What happened to you last night?

38:48.819 --> 38:51.617
Nothing. I finished my report, and I left.

38:51.989 --> 38:53.557
We heard a gunshot.

38:53.657 --> 38:55.017
I didn't.

38:55.117 --> 38:57.494
You certainly left in a mighty hurry.

38:57.786 --> 38:59.833
A call came in.

39:00.247 --> 39:01.523
Whats the matter with you, Father?

39:01.623 --> 39:03.500
You're beginning to sound like a cop.

39:04.001 --> 39:05.736
We found a body.

39:05.836 --> 39:07.883
It's left hand severed off.

39:08.338 --> 39:11.950
Maybe a cult of, uh,
weirdos out to cast a spell.

39:12.050 --> 39:13.702
Maybe a...

39:13.802 --> 39:16.396
group trying to appease
an angry god, huh Father?

39:16.972 --> 39:18.894
It's a possibility.

39:33.405 --> 39:35.452
(THUMPING)

39:43.373 --> 39:45.921
Wonder how that stuff looks in the ring.

39:46.585 --> 39:49.488
It has been a long time
since I've been in one.

39:49.588 --> 39:52.682
Let me see if I can find you
a sparring partner.

39:53.717 --> 39:54.826
All right.

39:54.926 --> 39:56.518
How about Hoyt?

39:57.054 --> 39:59.022
How about me?

40:00.432 --> 40:02.559
All right. You're on.

40:05.604 --> 40:08.402
(CROWD COACHING INDISTINCTLY)

40:38.970 --> 40:41.518
(CROWD COACHING INDISTINCTLY)

40:49.064 --> 40:50.531
(THUDS)

40:53.235 --> 40:54.702
(THUDS)

40:57.447 --> 40:58.823
(THUDS)

41:01.410 --> 41:02.661
(THUDS)

41:24.850 --> 41:27.318
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

41:46.329 --> 41:48.607
Are you all right? You're limping.

41:48.707 --> 41:50.609
Oh, a souvenir from the wars.

41:50.709 --> 41:54.174
It gets like this when I...
(CHUCKLES) when I overuse it.

41:55.380 --> 41:56.365
What can I do for you?

41:56.465 --> 41:58.342
Father, I need your help.

41:58.842 --> 42:02.095
Did you speak with Sargent Matson?

42:02.345 --> 42:05.223
Better than that. I fought with him.

42:05.557 --> 42:07.709
And he doesn't have any superhuman powers.

42:07.809 --> 42:09.777
It was a friendly match.

42:10.729 --> 42:14.758
Well, then the hand does not
possess Sargent Matson.

42:14.858 --> 42:16.301
Well, there's another line of reasoning.

42:16.401 --> 42:18.136
Oh, there is no hand. Right?

42:18.236 --> 42:20.222
Mrs. Baines. You're distraught.

42:20.322 --> 42:23.245
Grieved. Emotionally wrought.

42:24.409 --> 42:27.437
Father, I'm staying at the Cottage Inn.

42:27.537 --> 42:29.606
Bungalow 17. The number's on the card.

42:29.706 --> 42:33.585
And I'll be there
until I destroy the hand.

42:35.504 --> 42:40.931
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

42:59.528 --> 43:01.655
Excuse me, ma'am. Is this your car?

43:01.905 --> 43:04.975
Oh, hello.
It's, uh, Sargent Matson, isn't it?

43:05.075 --> 43:06.726
I asked about your car.

43:06.826 --> 43:09.229
Yeah, this is my car.
It's rented.

43:09.329 --> 43:10.480
Stolen.

43:10.580 --> 43:11.857
What?

43:11.957 --> 43:14.109
You can't be serious. You remember me.

43:14.209 --> 43:16.528
I met you with
Father Cunningham last night.

43:16.628 --> 43:19.990
I... excuse me, I mean, I have a rental
contract, if you want to see that.

43:20.090 --> 43:21.616
I'm not a car thief.

43:21.716 --> 43:24.286
Right now you're a suspect,
and suspects have to go to the station.

43:24.386 --> 43:26.329
Now, wait a minute.
I mean, have I got a choice?

43:26.429 --> 43:28.707
- We all have choices, ma'am.
- Well, you're not giving me any!

43:28.807 --> 43:31.668
- You're wasting time.
- You are making a big mistake.

43:31.768 --> 43:33.520
LEO: You're under arrest.

43:35.146 --> 43:36.647
Ow!

43:43.613 --> 43:45.182
What the hell is this all about?

43:45.282 --> 43:47.534
LEO:
You know what the hell it's all about.

43:47.742 --> 43:53.169
(EERIE MUSIC)

44:41.504 --> 44:43.782
Yes, Officer. What can I do for you?

44:43.882 --> 44:46.100
What do you want?

44:46.676 --> 44:50.767
Either you cut my hand off,
or I'll kill you.

44:53.475 --> 44:55.818
Why did she seek me out?

44:56.853 --> 44:59.401
Why did you send her to me?

45:00.315 --> 45:01.633
I want to help her.

45:01.733 --> 45:03.218
But how can I help her when I have so many

45:03.318 --> 45:06.287
of my own personal doubts?

45:07.197 --> 45:10.951
Father, I ask you for your strength
and your guidance.

45:21.127 --> 45:24.255
What are you gonna do with the hand?

45:25.382 --> 45:26.741
In a word...

45:26.841 --> 45:28.433
It's your gift.

45:28.718 --> 45:32.138
You set it free. Now it's yours.

45:49.030 --> 45:52.601
Uh uh. No straps, no gas,

45:52.701 --> 45:54.043
just cut.

45:59.249 --> 46:02.127
In the name of God, don't do it.

46:02.419 --> 46:05.593
In the name of evil, you and I must obey.

46:08.007 --> 46:09.492
DOCTOR: It's going to be very painful

46:09.592 --> 46:12.060
because this cauterizes and cuts.

46:12.679 --> 46:14.977
(BUZZING)

46:19.894 --> 46:21.441
God.

46:23.690 --> 46:27.660
- (GROANING)
- (SURGICAL TOOL BUZZING)

46:30.530 --> 46:33.032
(MOANING)

46:35.702 --> 46:38.204
(GROANING)

47:35.762 --> 47:37.684
(PHONE RINGING)

47:38.598 --> 47:40.458
VOICEOVER: Good evening. Cottage Inn.

47:40.558 --> 47:41.918
Bungalow 17, please.

47:42.018 --> 47:43.545
VOICEOVER: One moment, please.

47:43.645 --> 47:45.021
(PHONE RINGING)

47:48.107 --> 47:50.826
I'm sorry, Mrs. Baines
is not in her room yet.

47:51.736 --> 47:54.514
Would you tell her
that Father Cunningham called?

47:54.614 --> 47:58.435
And for her to give me a call,
no matter what time she comes in.

47:58.535 --> 48:00.662
VOICEOVER: Okay. Thank you, Father.

48:04.874 --> 48:08.002
(HEARTBEATS)

48:15.343 --> 48:17.095
Oh.

48:17.595 --> 48:19.096
No!

48:19.222 --> 48:20.473
(GUN FIRES)

48:27.564 --> 48:29.236
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

48:38.283 --> 48:40.160
DOCTOR: Let me help you.

48:45.331 --> 48:47.629
(CRUNCHING, RIPPING)

48:48.710 --> 48:51.486
- Oh, my God.
- Don't!

48:55.675 --> 48:58.018
Don't touch the hand!

49:00.388 --> 49:03.141
(DOCTOR GROANING)

49:10.899 --> 49:12.446
(THUNDERING)

49:14.485 --> 49:16.077
DOCTOR: Stop!

49:16.654 --> 49:18.531
(SCREAMS)

49:23.536 --> 49:25.037
(GRUNTS)

49:31.044 --> 49:33.421
(GROANING)

49:34.714 --> 49:40.141
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

49:56.778 --> 50:02.159
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

50:30.561 --> 50:32.187
(KEYS JINGLING)

50:54.168 --> 50:56.613
PATROLMAN: It was reported that
a patrol car was sitting here all night.

50:56.713 --> 50:58.135
Could be Matson's.

51:06.347 --> 51:07.749
This is Matson's car, all right.

51:07.849 --> 51:09.771
I'd better call headquarters.

51:16.024 --> 51:18.276
I wish I could have it,

51:19.068 --> 51:21.741
but it is yours, forever.

51:26.976 --> 51:32.003
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

51:44.260 --> 51:46.478
(BUZZING)

51:52.643 --> 51:58.070
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

52:05.364 --> 52:06.956
Oh, Father.

52:07.492 --> 52:10.370
Get me out of this nightmare.

52:10.495 --> 52:12.212
PATROLMAN: Hold it!

52:12.413 --> 52:14.381
DOCTOR: Let me go! (THUDS)

52:22.673 --> 52:24.140
(TIRES SCREECHING)

52:26.219 --> 52:27.641
(GUN FIRES)

52:28.846 --> 52:31.098
(TIRES SQUEALING)

52:32.600 --> 52:34.317
PATROLMAN: Quick, get in the car!

52:38.648 --> 52:42.027
(TIRES SQUEALING)

52:46.531 --> 52:48.999
(SIREN BLARING)

52:49.700 --> 52:55.127
(FAST-PACED MUSIC)

52:59.961 --> 53:02.008
(TIRES SCREECHING)

53:03.089 --> 53:05.307
(CRASHING)

53:07.635 --> 53:09.853
(SIRENS BLARING)

53:15.726 --> 53:17.398
(CRASHING)

53:21.858 --> 53:27.285
(INTENSE MUSIC)

53:49.552 --> 53:51.395
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

53:52.555 --> 53:57.982
(INTENSE MUSIC)

54:23.211 --> 54:25.133
(TIRES SCREECHING)

54:25.838 --> 54:27.510
(CRASHING)

54:34.931 --> 54:37.058
Ah!

54:50.363 --> 54:55.790
(HEART BEATING)

55:06.754 --> 55:09.006
FATHER CUNNINGHAM: You just take it easy.

55:09.131 --> 55:11.008
Call headquarters.

55:12.343 --> 55:17.770
(SLOW MUSIC)

55:27.608 --> 55:30.428
We gave it its freedom so...

55:30.528 --> 55:33.848
when Mark died, the hand became mine.

55:33.948 --> 55:36.601
Oh, it captured others, yes, but, uh...

55:36.701 --> 55:39.374
inevitably just to get back to me.

55:40.162 --> 55:42.915
I'd like to help you, Jennifer.

55:43.541 --> 55:45.860
You have helped, Father.

55:45.960 --> 55:47.320
Well, I mean, more than that.

55:47.420 --> 55:50.323
I mean, ultimately, to destroy this thing.

55:50.423 --> 55:51.890
Oh. (LAUGHS)

55:52.508 --> 55:54.118
The armor of religion?

55:54.218 --> 55:55.935
Sword of belief?

55:56.721 --> 55:58.623
That's part of it. Yes.

55:58.723 --> 56:00.270
Mm.

56:01.767 --> 56:05.020
Do you believe that there is a hand?

56:06.772 --> 56:08.883
Well, there's something.

56:08.983 --> 56:11.636
Do you think that this hand
will destroy me?

56:11.736 --> 56:14.534
JENNIFER:
It has others, who've been vulnerable.

56:14.989 --> 56:16.741
This right here.

56:24.540 --> 56:26.442
Well, you get some sleep.

56:26.542 --> 56:29.591
And I'll arrange
for police protection for you.

56:29.712 --> 56:33.261
Sleep won't help. Nor will the police.

56:34.383 --> 56:36.726
But you could pray for me.

56:49.231 --> 56:50.508
Father. There's a dying man.

56:50.608 --> 56:52.109
Can you administer last rites?

56:52.234 --> 56:53.405
You've got it.

56:55.571 --> 57:00.451
(SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC)

57:08.292 --> 57:10.009
PARAMEDIC: He's dead.

57:16.592 --> 57:18.765
(TV BLARING)

57:41.075 --> 57:42.747
Ah! (SCREAMS)

57:43.744 --> 57:45.996
(HEARTBEATS)

57:50.960 --> 57:56.387
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

57:57.758 --> 57:59.510
What's the matter?

58:01.595 --> 58:03.539
- Where's the coffin?
- It's destroyed!

58:03.639 --> 58:05.311
Come on. Let's go.

58:06.267 --> 58:11.694
(INTENSE MUSIC)

58:25.911 --> 58:31.338
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

59:06.535 --> 59:08.604
You'll find some clothes in here.

59:08.704 --> 59:10.626
You can change there.

59:17.963 --> 59:23.390
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

01:00:01.215 --> 01:00:03.934
(HEARTBEATS)

01:00:21.652 --> 01:00:22.970
Who are you calling?

01:00:23.070 --> 01:00:24.847
I'm trying to get through to the police.

01:00:24.947 --> 01:00:26.474
The police?

01:00:26.574 --> 01:00:28.601
What are they gonna do?
They gonna arrest it?

01:00:28.701 --> 01:00:30.394
Cite it? Try it for murder?

01:00:30.494 --> 01:00:32.021
You think they're gonna believe you?

01:00:32.121 --> 01:00:33.731
They'll believe me.

01:00:33.831 --> 01:00:35.566
They'll find it and destroy it.

01:00:35.666 --> 01:00:38.589
The hand will kill again.

01:00:41.755 --> 01:00:44.132
The phone. It's dead.

01:00:47.720 --> 01:00:49.847
Let's go into the church.

01:00:51.432 --> 01:00:56.859
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

01:01:07.281 --> 01:01:08.623
(DOOR SLAMS)

01:01:15.372 --> 01:01:20.799
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

01:01:29.762 --> 01:01:31.038
We're not safe here.

01:01:31.138 --> 01:01:33.106
Let's check the other doors. Come on.

01:01:33.682 --> 01:01:39.109
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

01:01:57.748 --> 01:02:00.967
(WIND WHISTLING AND GUSTING)

01:02:01.669 --> 01:02:03.796
(CHANDELIER CHAIN CREAKING)

01:02:16.016 --> 01:02:18.018
(WIND STOPS)

01:02:31.782 --> 01:02:33.829
(DOOR CREAKING)

